The paper deals with relation extraction, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and information extraction (IE). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel framework that uses embedding techniques to learn distributed representations of context, which is a common approach in machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI the second likely category. The paper also involves iterative learning, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with information retrieval (IR) as it involves extracting information from unstructured text data. Finally, the paper also involves knowledge base (KB) and domain heuristics, which are common in database (cs.DB) research.
